This article is a transcript of a speech given by President Joe Biden at the Hylton Performing Arts Center in Manassas, Virginia. The speech focused on defending women's rights, particularly the right to choose, in light of the recent Supreme Court decision in the Dobbs case. Biden criticized former President Donald Trump and Republicans for their efforts to restrict access to abortion and pledged to veto any national abortion ban if Congress were to pass one. He called on the audience to take action, vote in the upcoming elections, and work towards restoring the protections of Roe v. Wade. The speech also touched on other issues such as healthcare and the broader rights of privacy.